HEADWORD: Self-sacrifice
<hw>Self`-sac"ri*fice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
sacrificing one's self, or one's interest, for others;
self-devotion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

